<A HREF='B19C061.htm'>Psalms 61</A></P><CENTER><H2 ALIGN=CENTER>The Book of     
Psalms</H2></CENTER><P><A HREF='index.htm'>Return to Index</A>.</P><CENTER>     
<TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=5 WIDTH=90%><TR><TD></TD><TD><CENTER><H1>Chapter    
62</H1></CENTER></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V1><H4>1</H4></TD><TD><P>  
Truly my soul waiteth upon ELOHIYM: from him cometh my salvation.</P></TD></TR> 
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V2><H4>2</H4></TD><TD><P>He only is my rock and my   
salvation; he is my defence; I shall not be greatly moved.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD 
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V3><H4>3</H4></TD><TD><P>How long will ye imagine mischief   
against a man? ye shall be slain all of you: as a bowing wall shall ye be, and  
as a tottering fence.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V4><H4>4</H4></TD>
<TD><P>They only consult to cast him down from his excellency: they delight in  
lies: they bless with their mouth, but they curse inwardly. Selah.</P></TD></TR>
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V5><H4>5</H4></TD><TD><P>My soul, wait thou only     
upon ELOHIYM; for my expectation is from him.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP>  
<A NAME=V6><H4>6</H4></TD><TD><P>He only is my rock and my salvation: he is my  
defence; I shall not be moved.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V7><H4>  
7</H4></TD><TD><P>In ELOHIYM is my salvation and my glory: the rock of my       
strength, and my refuge, is in ELOHIYM.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A      
NAME=V8><H4>8</H4></TD><TD><P>Trust in him at all times; ye people, pour out    
your heart before him: ELOHIYM is a refuge for us. Selah.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD  
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V9><H4>9</H4></TD><TD><P>Surely men of low degree are        
vanity, and men of high degree are a lie: to be laid in the balance, they are   
altogether lighter than vanity.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V10><H4>
10</H4></TD><TD><P>Trust not in oppression, and become not vain in robbery: if  
riches increase, set not your heart upon them.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP> 
<A NAME=V11><H4>11</H4></TD><TD><P>ELOHIYM hath spoken once; twice have I heard 
this; that power belongeth unto ELOHIYM.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A     
NAME=V12><H4>12</H4></TD><TD><P>Also unto thee, O ADONAY, belongeth mercy: for  
thou renderest to every man according to his work.</P></TD></TR></TABLE>        
